snippet.textDisplay:
I feel honored to have played this game. The world-building was excellent. I feel like I’m friends with all the characters—I can imagine myself living in this world; I can taste and smell the water and the air.
The music immerses you so deeply that all it takes is to close your eyes and you’re in Lumière.
What a game, what incredible dedication.
snippet.textOriginal:
I feel honored to have played this game. The world-building was excellent. I feel like I’m friends with all the characters—I can imagine myself living in this world; I can taste and smell the water and the air.
The music immerses you so deeply that all it takes is to close your eyes and you’re in Lumière.
What a game, what incredible dedication.

snippet.textDisplay:
It is by far my favorite game of all time and thats with 30 years of gaming experience. I grew up with Zelda's Awakening as my first game and always held an insane amount of respect for music in games since then. 
Golden Sun, MGS and Tales of Symphonia ebbed the way just further that music is everything and since then I never respected games without good music anymore. 
IT HAS BECOME SO NEGLIGENT to put amazing music and voice acting in a game when it is PARAMOUNT to gameplay and storytelling to give it atmosphere and soul. 
Everyone in Kepler and Sandfall should be proud to have pathed a new gaming era for us to come where developers might think twice what to prioritize in their game. 
This has become a star in gaming history that no one will ever forget.

snippet.textDisplay:
I bought this game just out of pure coincidence. I was so saturated with typical triple A games and wanted to go more indie.
So I heard of this game, the title interested me and what I got, blew my off my socks.
It is my personal Game of the Year, but I would be disappointed, if that game didn't win at LEAST best OST.
Everytime I hear that soundtrack I get goosebumps and tears start rolling, it is just so beautiful.

Thank you to EVERYONE at Sandfall interactive for that absolute wonderful peace of a video game as well as a very very emotional soundtrack.

Love you all <3

snippet.textDisplay: I used to dislike my name (Alicia) for most of my life. Even though I live in the French-speaking part of Belgium, I never met anyone else with the same name. I always felt like the pronunciation sounded strange—especially when English speakers pronounce it like “a-lee-shah,” which I really hate! Growing up, a girl once even told me that "Alice" sounded better... That didn’t help. But thanks to this game, I finally feel represented, if that makes sense. So thank you, Sandfall!
snippet.textOriginal: I used to dislike my name (Alicia) for most of my life. Even though I live in the French-speaking part of Belgium, I never met anyone else with the same name. I always felt like the pronunciation sounded strange—especially when English speakers pronounce it like “a-lee-shah,” which I really hate! Growing up, a girl once even told me that "Alice" sounded better... That didn’t help. But thanks to this game, I finally feel represented, if that makes sense. So thank you, Sandfall!

snippet.textDisplay:
Lot tryed translate so gathered some clue : The song “Alicia” is written in a pseudo-Occitan or Occitan-inspired conlang — a constructed poetic language designed to mimic the rhythm and emotion of Medieval Occitan (spoken in southern France during the 12th–14th centuries). It was intentionally created to carry emotional weight while hiding narrative meaning, which is only revealed later in the game .
This approach is common in storytelling-focused games — for example:
Shadow of the Colossus used a fictional language blending Japanese and Latin tones
NieR Replicant featured songs in “Chaos Language,” built for mood over meaning

In “Alicia,” the invented lyrics help preserve the mystery of the story while evoking southern French identity, memory, and loss. so you need bit of imagination can be something like this:
[Verse]
What did you leave behind?
I am forsaken.
The child is lost.
The fire, the veil, the canvas.
The child is gone.

[Chorus]
Maelle is calling.
The memory of us fades.
Alicia is calling.
Verso is breaking.
Lune is here.

[Verse]
What have you let go of?
I am forsaken.
The child is lost.
The fire, the veil, the canvas.
The child is gone.

[Chorus]
Maelle is calling.
The memory of us fades.
Alicia is calling.
Verso is breaking.
Lune is here.

snippet.textDisplay:
Il suffit de lire les commentaires venus des quatre coins du monde, déversant leur amour, pour comprendre. Clair Obscur n’est pas qu’un jeu. C’est une expérience, un souffle, un instant suspendu dans le temps qui touche l’âme.  Nous ne le savions pas, mais nous avions besoin de cette traversée, de cette poésie, de cette lumière au milieu de l’ombre. Parfois, il naît des œuvres qui bouleversent... Celle-ci, elle, élève.
Et je crois, humblement, pouvoir dire merci… au nom de tous ceux qui ont rêvé, pleuré, aimé…en marchant à travers ce jet d’encre, cette toile , ce chef-d’œuvre.
snippet.textOriginal:

Et bon si c'est le 3e, Ragnarok je serai vraiment surpris mais curieux de voir tes reproches.

snippet.textDisplay: Dude, I lost my father about 2 years ago, as a victim of suicide, and this game and the story behind it, made me feel very welcomed... I would like to talk more about it, but I will try not to give too many spoilers... but I was very happy playin the game, and at the end of the game, you have a certain path that you can choose, without wanting to spoil too much, but I wanted to stay longer in the game, I was able to understand all the feelings that the game wanted to convey and I didn't want it all to end, whoever finished it, understood what It meant... and I almost made a choice that theoretically would be wrong, because of a feeling that I also had... I prolonged the ending until the last moment and when the final decision of the game came and appeared, I spent about 10 minutes reflecting... and I was like "wow, I can understand both choices"... and after I made a certain choice and saw the prologue, I thought, "we have to accept things as they are, and not as we want them to be..." and I simply got a tattoo to make a mask of one of the characters in the game to do on my arm... this game really touched me... for me,this game is meant to be forever in my heart and in my skin, to remember that we cannot change the thins, when someone falls, we continue... I can completely understand Alicia's feelings, SPOILER...... just like Alicia, I understand the feeling of wanting to stay in that reality forever, and of feeling guilty for something that wasn't your fault

snippet.textDisplay:
Cette musique est représentative de ce que le jeux vidéo doit nous fournir pour emmener un scénario et nous toucher.

Il est très acceptable de faire comprendre que la musique est intemporelle et éternelle permet de nombreuses choses comme toucher des gens franchir des émotions pour faire comprendre au monde entier que nous avons tous un cœur que nous soyons une femme un homme un enfant ou voir même un animal.

Il est le plus beau thème du jeu vidéo musicalement parlant que j'ai entendu jusqu'à présent au-delà même de ce que Nintendo ou square-enix on pu nous faire écouter jusqu'à présent.

autant le jeu à une sobriété sonore des détails ahurissants qui font frémir à l'oreille chaque coup chaque parole chaque image apporte une émotion c'est quelque chose de jamais rêver jusqu'à présent et ça ne m'étonne pas qu'il dépasse un jour ou l'autre les plus de 10000000 d'exemplaires.

c'est tout ce que nous demandions depuis très longtemps il y a pas besoin d'avoir des 1000000 d'euros mais faire parler la passion c'est la seule chose qui reste idéal pour qu'ensuite nous pouvons soutenir sans parler en plus du très bon prix, là où tout augmente c'est juste un combo parfait un jeu magnifique des musiques qui resteront à jamais gravés dans nos mémoire et coeur de joueur et on espère une suite et une venue au cinéma bravo superbe musique et très bon compositeur et chanteuse.

Vivement les Games World pour que vous puissiez être élu musique et jeux de l'année amplement mérité et je le dis avec toute sincérité merci et encore merci, de nous avoir montré au monde entier de la douceur là où l'ombre se pose car les émotions ont franchi la planète.

Cela ne m'étonnerait pas de voir Microsoft vous proposez, une offre pour que vous puissiez faire partie des (Xbox Game Studio)
belle pioche du Xbox Game Pass pour le cout, la ou il été en rupture de stock partout, l'abonnement a permis d'etre accueillante pour nous, finalement ce n'est pas si mauvais. 

De la part d'un passionnée de music et de jeux video.

C’est tout le temps juste, ça tombe tout le temps en plein dans le mille. C’est fou de voir que ce sont tous des jeunes. Franchement ça fait vraiment chaud au cœur de voir qu’il y a encore de vrai passionnés dans cette industrie. Par pitié ne vous perdez pas. Ce jeu et tout ce qui le compose est un chef d’œuvre. Tout le monde dit GOTY, non c’est plus que ça encore, c’est l’un des meilleurs jeu jamais fait

snippet.textDisplay:
What I like about is this song, is the expression of the singer.

The song is sad and give some sort of despair. But seeing Alice Duport-Percier sing it at the same time multiply those sentiments.

She isn't simply singing something beautiful. She's *living* the song, in a personal way, to a point that she looks "haunted" at the end, just by singing it,.

PS : I don't know if "haunted" is the right word to say here, if any english speaker know abtter one, please enlighten this frenchman here.

snippet.textDisplay:
Honestly this game feels like it does not belong in our current timeline of gaming. Its polished, complete, very fair priced and you can unlock almost everything by just playing the game. The music, the story, the world, ... almost everything is so crazy good. How is that even possible. 

Yes...your success will also be the end...like with everything else things get worse if they get popular and the company behind it gets bigger with more shareholders and less detication and love behind it.

But I will 100 % enjoy everything there is to enjoy before that happens. 🎉 Thank you for this masterpiece of gaming culture.

snippet.textDisplay:
Mrs. Duport-Percier – I've been following your career for many years, ever since you worked with the Grissini Project. It makes my heart soar to see and hear you perform. You deserve all the praise in the world.
To Mr. Testard and the rest of the ensemble – hats off, good people. You’ve rocked my world and, I’m sure of it, the world of many others as well. 🙌

I first heard this theme when the original trailer was released, and it made my heart skip a beat. I knew this game would be something special just from seeing and hearing the first 16 seconds of the video. Then, when the full version of "Alicia" was published, it instantly became a daily must-listen for me and my six-year-old daughter, Alicja. Once I started the game and reached the main menu, it took me a long time to decide I was ready to stop listening and begin the adventure.

I wish all games were made with such care and respect for the musical aspect of the medium.
snippet.textOriginal:

To Mr. Testard and the rest of the ensemble – hats off, good people. You’ve rocked my world and, I’m sure of it, the world of many others as well. 🙌

I first heard this theme when the original trailer was released, and it made my heart skip a beat. I knew this game would be something special just from seeing and hearing the first 16 seconds of the video. Then, when the full version of "Alicia" was published, it instantly became a daily must-listen for me and my six-year-old daughter, Alicja. Once I started the game and reached the main menu, it took me a long time to decide I was ready to stop listening and begin the adventure.

I wish all games were made with such care and respect for the musical aspect of the medium.

25 years as a video gamer, I’ve sunk tons of time and money and the greater majority of my lifetime into games, and Clair Obscure Expedition 33 is absolutely the most masterful game I’ve ever experienced. Game of the year in my eyes. The music haunts my soul on repeat when I’m not playing it. 

And the game…my god the game… play it. If you are even THINKING about playing it, like even if the chance is 0.01% that you might play it, PLAY IT. This is a once in a lifetime game, and everywhere I go everyone is being respectful of spoilers because of truly how good this game is. 

Don’t. Miss. This. Start your expedition today.

snippet.textDisplay:
I wish the last act in Expedition33 wasn't about an addicted child's fight with her father, but was related to the world of the map. Because in the beginning you get a completely different plot connected with this beautiful and interesting world, and at the end the plot is about something else. You get a dissonance. I came to play one thing - and at the end of the other in terms of the story :(

I would dream of a ‘clean ending’ - where they ‘clean up’ everything unnecessary at the canvas, returning it to what it was - without the creations of his mother and father, without Maelle and the split, without the whole generation of people (including Gustave and the others). That is, to a state where only the interesting and bizarre creatures created by Verso live. And the canvas itself is sent under the lock of a safe with no way to get there. Isn't it a sorrowful and sad ending, which, nevertheless, is not reduced to a banal addiction to the virtual world, but teaches to appreciate and not to interfere in other people's creations, even if it can temporarily help with the grief of loss?

snippet.textDisplay:
Je ne sais pas si ce message sera lu un jour par l'équipe derriere ce jeux, mais grand merci a vous, vous nous avez donné une oeuvre d'art, a tous les niveaux :
- Les musiques
- L'histoire
- Les émotions 

Ca fait une trentaine d'année que je joue a des jeux, et je crois bien que c'est la première fois que je ressens autant d'émotions !

Merci encore pour tout et a tous !

--

A big thank you for the whole team behind this video game, which is even more than a video game, it's Art !

Everything is a masterpiece :
- The musics
- The story
- The emotions

I've been playing for more than 30 years, and i think it's the very first time i feel so much emotions !

Thanks again for all you've done, all of you.

snippet.textDisplay: My cat crossed Rainbow bridge in April before this game is released. by the age of 14 she passed away from pancreas failure. so that I have deep empathy on this game's theme that is revealed on its climax - Loss. there are still two different thoughts are conflicting in my mind - let it go or want to be with her in any way. this is why two progagonists' choices resonate with me. but anyway, as the most quoted phrase goes, 'Tomorrow comes.' I should get over it and carry on somehow. Thus I chose Expedition 33 as GOTY 2025.

snippet.textDisplay:
I have a soft spot for soundtracks. In most cases—maybe 70% of the time—a powerful OST is all it takes to carry me through a game.
With this one, my love began the moment that song was released.
The weight of every word… it was overwhelming. Beautiful. Painful.
But then you play the game—and you realize the pain isn’t just in the lyrics. It’s in the story. It’s in the atmosphere. It’s in the quiet, beautiful moments that ache just as much as the tragic ones.
This game deserves its crown. It’s GOTY material. It belongs in the hall of the greatest games of the past nine years.
And Lumiere… Lumiere deserves to live on.

snippet.textDisplay: Playing Clair Obscur for the first time left me absolutely speechless. From the moment I stepped into its hauntingly beautiful world, every note of its soundtrack sent shivers down my spine and painted my imagination with pure wonder. The music isn’t just background—it’s a living, breathing character that guides you through shadows and light, and each melody hit me with such emotional power that I found myself whispering ‘wow’ over and over again.
snippet.textOriginal: Playing Clair Obscur for the first time left me absolutely speechless. From the moment I stepped into its hauntingly beautiful world, every note of its soundtrack sent shivers down my spine and painted my imagination with pure wonder. The music isn’t just background—it’s a living, breathing character that guides you through shadows and light, and each melody hit me with such emotional power that I found myself whispering ‘wow’ over and over again.

snippet.textDisplay:
It's really good to see The Grissini Project (Italian Breadsticks) and Orchestra Curieux (Curiosity Orchestra) receive some of their dues!

For those that are not aware, Ms. Duport-Percier, the vocalist here, as well as the instrumentalists have been covering video game and anime music for years now at a very professional level. Their covers include The Witcher, Final Fantasy XV, Nier Automata, Legend of Zelda, and Studio Ghibli. I believe they are French-speakers (Ils parlent Francais) from Switzerland (Suisse). Presumably, they all go to the same elite music school. In my personal opinion, they are among the best, if not the best, kept secret of unrecognized talent that YouTube has to offer. 

I fully agree with the fellow comment (from @Roze_aye) that this song NEEDS to be performed at the game awards!
-Jon from Canada.

snippet.textDisplay:
En tant que Montpelliérain de 33 ans, j'ai été profondément ému par Clair Obscur: Expedition 33. Dès son annonce, j'ai immédiatement précommandé le jeu, convaincu par la vision artistique de Sandfall Interactive, notre studio local.​

Chaque note de la bande-son, composée par Lorien Testard, m'a touché, chaque scène m'a transporté. Le jeu m'a offert une échappée belle, un moment suspendu où j'ai pu penser à autre chose. Cela faisait bien longtemps que je n'avais pas ressenti une telle émotion.​

Un immense merci à toute l'équipe de Sandfall Interactive pour cette œuvre magistrale. Votre travail a donné vie à un scénario poignant et une expérience inoubliable.

snippet.textDisplay:
Merci ! Ce n'est pas grand chose mais mon esprit et mon âme s'est senti toucher par vos musique et ce jeux m'a définitivement réconcilier avec le tour par tour que j'avais abandonné depuis FF 10, si vous faites une série animé, la suite du jeux etc avec autant de beauté dans l'écriture je prendrai les yeux fermés !
Tout est juste bien dosé.
Et un giga méga bravo à TOUT LE MONDE, l'équipe française fout une PUT... de claque à des grosses licence, je vous dit bonnes continuation et continuez à nous régaler !
Je retourne sur le jeux je veux faire chaque mètres carrés avec mon hom cinéma. 😍

snippet.textDisplay:
Dommage que le jeu sortent en 2025 et pas 2024. Il va surement manquer le GOTY du fait qu'il va y avoir GTA 6 cette année. Par contre quel BO qui prend au tripes. J'espère à minima que vous gagnerez tous les prix d'une meilleures BO pour un jeu vidéo au Game Award.

Ce jeu mérite d'etre joué par un maximum de joueur tellement il vous mettra un claque. Surtout quant on voit les ribambelle de jeux AAA sans ames et sans saveur qui sont générique.

Ouais voila si on devait retenir qu'un mot, ce jeu a une ame et la BO contribue beaucoup à cela.

Félicitation à toute l'equipe

snippet.textDisplay: Le jeu est incroyable ❤, et la musique participe grandement à l’ambiance. Les jeux sont très différents, mais elle me rappelle NieR Automata (que j’avais aussi adoré). BRAVO et MERCI pour ce chef d’œuvre!!❤

Sandfall, vous avez pondu une absolue MASTERCLASS. Tout est incroyable, et les musiques, bon sang... Ca fait 20 ans que je me bute sur les jeux videos et que j'y perd le goût et la saveur à ne plus les finir.

Pour la première fois depuis presque 10 de ces 20 années j'ai terminé le jeu et je vais encore le refaire, pour la première fois je suis resté bouche bée devant l'écran titre ou une musique du jeu, à l'écouter pendant 10, 20 voir 30 minutes.

Incroyable.

snippet.textDisplay:
Ce jeu je n'en attendais rien ! Je n'avais regardé que 2/3 vidéos trailer dessus, ni écouté de music. Je ne savais même pas si j'aller l'acheter. Je l'es acheté sur un coup de tète et je ne le regrette absolument pas ! Quelle merveille ! Tout est super bien travaillé et bien fait ! Les graphismes, les animations super bien fait, les musiques qui t'arrache presque une larme a chaque fois et le gameplay jouissif si t'es bon et dure si tu l'es moins. Tout ça pour 50 euros :).

Je voulais vous dire MERCI !!! Merci de me montré que le VRAIE RPG n'est pas mort ! Merci de foutre une claque a Square Enix en leurs montrant c'est quoi un vraie RPG, ceux qu'ils ne savent plus faire depuis très très longtemps.

Pour moi ce seras le jeu qui va tout rafler cette année ou presque et je l'espère car il le mérite !

snippet.textDisplay:
my  translation: 

Kasoi dalé u
The heavens weep.

Moi dané
And I, too, am swept away.

Goséi dané
And so are you.

Kala soika tovla
As if time itself has frozen.

Goséi moéto
With you... only with you.

Maella itade nai
Maella is no longer here.

Dosokémo naémai
Yet hope lingers still.

Alicia itade nai
Alicia, too, is gone.

Verso édaéké
And our words scatter into the winds.

Lune ai
Oh, the aching moon!

You could play this song to the rich and snobby crowd - while withholding info that this is a *game* soundtrack - and I'm sure they won't know any wiser.

Seriously, I haven't been this moved since first listening to the Destiny/Destiny 2 soundtrack.

If this soundtrack doesn't win the best soundtrack award in the 2025 competition, I'll be *severely* disappointed.
